description: Kottayam couple and friend found dead in Arunachal hotel under mysterious circumstances. Autopsy pending. Kerala police investigating. Allegations of black magic. Victims were Ayurveda doctors and a teacher.

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the benchmark equity indices for Indian stock markets, opened in red on Wednesday. BSE Sensex dropped over 300 and Nifty50 dipped below 22,400 level.  The tech view suggests that a breakthrough above 22500-22600 levels could lead to further gains for Nifty.
title: BSE Sensex drops over 300 points, Nifty50 below 21,400 level

description: In addition to reversing a dismal campaign, where MI has suffered three consecutive losses, captain Hardik must rally the support of the Wankhede Stadium crowd. Historically, the crowd has served as MI's twelfth player, their fervent energy turning seemingly dire situations into victories for the five-time champions over the years.

description: Tihar Jail guards are vigilant over potential harm to Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal by fame-seeking inmates. In Jail No. 2, Srikan Ramaswami was murdered in a gang war linked to a 2015 murder case. The court transferred the investigation to CBI, and Kejriwal is in judicial custody until April 15.

description: The US strongly opposes China's renaming of Arunachal Pradesh. India also firmly rejects Beijing's 'shameless' attempts and says that assigning invented names will not alter the reality that Arunachal Pradesh is, has been, and will always be an integral and inalienable part of India. Kiren Rijiju criticizes China's actions. PM Modi's development work in border areas was praised.
title: US ‘strongly opposes’ China’s renaming of places in Arunachal

description: In the fiscal year 2023-24, the construction of national highways (NH) extended to approximately 12,300 kilometers, averaging about 34 kilometers per day. This achievement marks the second-highest rate of NH construction in the nation's history. The highest recorded thus far was in 2020-21, with construction reaching 13,327 kilometers at a pace of 36.5 kilometers per day.
title: National highways construction touched 34 km per day in 2023-24

description: Amit Shah distinguishes BJP from INDIA bloc, praising PM Modi's dedication and setting a 60% vote target. He criticizes opposition leaders and corruption, expressing confidence in BJP's electoral success.

description: The BJP-JD(S) alliance aims to win all 28 Lok Sabha seats in Karnataka, a feat only achieved by Congress in 1971. Despite no dominant national party, Karnataka's political landscape remains competitive with a history of regional party building efforts.
title: LS polls: In 17 elections, only once has a party swept all seats in Karnataka

description: KL Rahul applauded Mayank Yadav's fiery pace as LSG secured back-to-back IPL 2024 victories. Yadav's exceptional bowling performance against RCB propelled LSG to success. Rahul humorously remarked that he preferred witnessing the 21-year-old's bowling prowess from the safety of 20 yards behind the stumps rather than facing him with a bat in hand.

description: SEBI has made it compulsory for investors to complete Know Your Client (KYC) formalities before investing in mutual fund schemes. It is important to note that starting from April 1, bank statements or utility bills will no longer be considered valid documents for completing the KYC process.

description: “Under Crooked Joe Biden, every state is now a border state. Every town is now a border town because Joe Biden has brought the carnage and chaos and killing from all over world and dumped it straight into our backyards,” Trump said in Grand Rapids, where he stood flanked by law enforcement officers in uniform before a line of flags.

description: An earthquake offshore Taiwan with a magnitude of 7.2 rocked the capital Taipei on Wednesday morning, knocking out power in several parts of the city and sparking a tsunami warning for the islands of southern Japan and the Philippines. Taiwan television stations showed footage of some collapsed buildings in the eastern county of Hualien, near the quake's epicentre, and media reported some people were trapped.
